    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into large bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-chicken-balti-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-chicken-balti-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [300ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-chicken-balti-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pod[s]</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-chicken-balti-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>chicken </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-chicken-balti-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 150ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [225ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>chicken stock</strong></p><p>Once the vegetables have softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and your<strong> ginger paste </strong>to the pan</p><p>Add your <strong>garam masala</strong>, <strong>ground paprika</strong>, <strong>crushed cardamom pod[s]</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong> and <strong>ground cumin</strong> with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-chicken-balti-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, increase the heat to high, then add the <strong>chopped chicken</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until the chicken has browned</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken stock </strong>and your <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened to a curry-like consistency \u2013 this is your<strong> fragrant chicken balti</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-chicken-balti-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>fragrant</strong> <strong>chicken balti</strong> with the <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Tip: Watch out for any cardamom pods!</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
